#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:1
msgid "Object serialization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:2
msgid ""
"Modules which have `INCLUDE_MARSHAL` in their `vtk.module` will opt their "
"headers into the automated code generation of (de)serializers. Only classes "
"which are annotated by the `VTK_MARSHALAUTO` wrapping hint will have "
"generated serialization code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:4
msgid "Marshalling Hints"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:6
msgid "Classes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:8
msgid ""
"VTK auto generates (de)serialization code in C++ for classes annotated by "
"the `VTK_MARSHALAUTO` wrapping hint. Additionally, classes that are "
"annotated with `VTK_MARSHALMANUAL` require manual code. Please refer to "
"[manual-marshal-code](#manual-marshal-code) which explains everything you "
"need to consider when opting out of the automated marshalling code "
"generation process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:13
msgid "Properties"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:15
msgid "Excluding properties"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:17
msgid ""
"You can exclude certain properties of a class by simply annotating the "
"relevant setter/getter functions with `VTK_MARSHALEXCLUDE(reason)`, where "
"reason is one of `VTK_MARSHAL_EXCLUDE_REASON_IS_INTERNAL` or "
"`VTK_MARSHAL_EXCLUDE_REASON_NOT_SUPPORTED`. This reason will be printed in "
"the generated C++ source code explaining why the property was not serialized."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:22
msgid "Custom get/set functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:24
msgid ""
"Some properties may not be correctly recognized by the property parser "
"because they have different names for their get and set functions. You can "
"override this by annotating the get function with the "
"`VTK_MARSHALGETTER(property)` macro. Doing so will ensure that the function "
"gets recognized as a getter for `property`. `VTK_MARSHALSETTER(property)` "
"serves a similar purpose."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:30
msgid "Automated code generation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:31
msgid ""
"The `vtkWrapSerDes` executable makes use of the `WrappingTools` package to "
"automatically generate:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:33
msgid "A serializer function with signature:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:36
#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:46
msgid "Generated only for classes annotated by `VTK_MARSHALAUTO` macro"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:39
msgid ""
"static nlohmann:json Serialize_vtkClassName(vtkObjectBase*, vtkSerializer*)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:43
msgid "A deserializer function with signature:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:49
msgid ""
"static bool Deserialize_vtkClassName(const nlohmann::json&, vtkObjectBase*, "
"vtkDeserializer*)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:53
msgid "A invoker function with signature:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:56
msgid ""
"Generated for classes annotated by `VTK_MARSHALAUTO` or `VTK_MARSHALMANUAL` "
"macro"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:59
msgid ""
"static nlohmann::json Invoke_vtkClassName(vtkInvoker* invoker, "
"vtkObjectBase* objectBase, const char* methodName, nlohmann::json args)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:63
msgid "A registrar function that registers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:64
msgid "the serializer function with a serializer instance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:65
msgid "the deserializer function with a deserializer instance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:66
msgid "the constructor of the VTK class with a deserializer instance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:67
msgid "Here is an example for the class `vtkObject`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:69
msgid ""
"int RegisterHandlers_vtkObjectSerDes(void* ser, void* deser, void* invoker)\n"
"{\n"
"  int success = 0;\n"
"  if (auto* asObjectBase = static_cast<vtkObjectBase*>(ser))\n"
"  {\n"
"    if (auto* serializer = vtkSerializer::SafeDownCast(asObjectBase))\n"
"    {\n"
"      serializer->RegisterHandler(typeid(vtkObject), Serialize_vtkObject);\n"
"      success = 1;\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"  if (auto* asObjectBase = static_cast<vtkObjectBase*>(deser))\n"
"  {\n"
"    if (auto* deserializer = vtkDeserializer::SafeDownCast(asObjectBase))\n"
"    {\n"
"      deserializer->RegisterHandler(typeid(vtkObject), "
"Deserialize_vtkObject);\n"
"      deserializer->RegisterConstructor(\"vtkObject\", []() { return "
"vtkObject::New(); });\n"
"      success = 1;\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"  if (auto* asObjectBase = static_cast<vtkObjectBase*>(invoker))\n"
"  {\n"
"    if (auto* invokerObject = vtkDeserializer::SafeDownCast(asObjectBase))\n"
"    {\n"
"      invokerObject->RegisterHandler(typeid(vtkObject), Invoke_vtkObject);\n"
"      success = 1;\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"  return success;\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:102
msgid "Manual marshal code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:104
msgid ""
"On the other hand, the `VTK_MARSHALMANUAL` macro is used to indicate that a "
"class will take part in marshalling, but it cannot trivially (de)serialize "
"it's properties. This is because one or more of the class's properties may "
"not have an appropriate setter/getter function that is recognized by the VTK "
"property parser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:109
msgid ""
"For such classes, a developer is expected to provide the code to serialize "
"and deserialize the class in `vtkClassNameSerDesHelper.cxx` That file must "
"satisfy these conditions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:112
msgid "It must live in the same module as `vtkClassName`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:113
msgid ""
"It must export a function `int "
"RegisterHandlers_vtkClassNameSerDesHelper(void*, void*, void*)` with C "
"linkage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:114
msgid ""
"It must define and declare the `static` functions from [automated-code-"
"generation](#automated-code-generation)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:115
msgid ""
"Finally, it must implement the helper function "
"`RegisterHandlers_vtkClassNameSerDesHelper` to register your handlers with "
"the object manager. Please see the `RegisterHandlers_vtkObjectSerDes` sample "
"code in [automated-code-generation](#automated-code-generation) for guidance "
"on implementing this helper."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:118
msgid "Example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:120
msgid ""
"int RegisterHandlers_vtkClassNameSerDesHelper(void* ser, void* deser, void* "
"invoker)\n"
"{\n"
"  // See RegisterHandlers_vtkObjectSerDes for what must go here.\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:127
msgid "that registers:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:128
msgid "a serializer function with a serializer instance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:129
msgid "a deserializer function with a deserializer instance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:130
msgid "a constructor of the VTK class with a deserializer instance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:131
msgid ""
"Optionally, a function that can call methods by name on an object with an "
"invoker instance. The wrapping tool automatically generates this code even "
"for classes annotated by `VTK_MARSHALMANUAL`. You can overwrite that in your "
"custom `RegisterHandlers_vtkClassNameSerDesHelper`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:135
msgid "Marshal hint macro"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:136
msgid ""
"Classes which are annotated with `VTK_MARSHALAUTO` are considered by the "
"`vtkWrapSerDes` executable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:137
msgid ""
"Classes annotated with `VTK_MARSHALMANUAL` are hand coded in the same "
"module. Here are some examples:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:138
msgid ""
"`Common/Core/vtkCollectionSerDesHelper.cxx` for `Common/Core/vtkCollection.h`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:139
msgid ""
"`Common/DataModel/vtkCellArraySerDesHelper.cxx` for `Common/DataModel/"
"vtkCellArray.h`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:141
msgid "Convenient script to annotate headers and module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:142
msgid ""
"The [Utilities/Marshalling/marshal_macro_annotate_headers.py](../../../"
"Utilities/Marshalling/marshal_macro_annotate_headers.py) script annotates "
"headers for automatic or manual serialization. It is fed and driven by the "
"accompanying [Utilities/Marshalling/VTK_MARSHALAUTO.txt](../../../Utilities/"
"Marshalling/VTK_MARSHALAUTO.txt), [Utilities/Marshalling/VTK_MARSHALMANUAL."
"txt](../../../Utilities/Marshalling/VTK_MARSHALMANUAL.txt) and [Utilities/"
"Marshalling/ignore.txt](../../../Utilities/Marshalling/ignore.txt)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:144
msgid ""
"When the `-u, --update` argument is used, headers are in-place edited to use "
"the `VTK_MARSHAL(AUTO|MANUAL)` wrapping hint. Files that already have this "
"hint are untouched."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:146
msgid ""
"When the `-t, --test` argument is used, the source tree is checked for "
"inconsistent use of marshal macros."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:148
msgid "Testing serialization code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_serialization.md:150
msgid ""
"Serialization testing can be run on top of regular VTK C++ regression tests "
"by performing an image comparison test after serializing and deserializing "
"the test's render window. When VTK is configured with "
"`VTK_WRAP_SERIALIZAITON=ON`, serialization tests will be generated with the "
"suffix `SerDes`. Specific tests can be excluded from serialization testing "
"by adding the `NO_SERDES` argument to the test in `Some/Module/Testing/Cxx/"
"CMakeLists.txt`."
msgstr ""
